        "action": "Fund free dental treatment on the NHS for all cancer patients on treatment",
        "additional_details": "",
        "background": "Unfortunately, on average 400,000 people are diagnosed with cancer each year in the uk.\r\nSome drugs used in treatment can affect the teeth and jaws.\r\nThis is why dental treatment should be on the NHS for the duration of treatment.",
